CNCP v1 24149
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#6080: Root comment breaking the `<Transition>` without any warning",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:09.079697+00:00",
  "text": "Root comment breaking the `<Transition>` without any warning\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.2.37\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://sfc.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nClick the `Toggle` button twice, the `<Home>` component missing.\n\n### What is expected?\n\n`<Home>` and `<About>` components can be switched back and forth.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nWhen switch to `<About>` component with root comment, `<Transition>` breaking.\r\n\r\nConsole does not have any warning.\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nI think it should log a warning to admonish this usage, if this is a limitation.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "scope: transition"
  ],
